# Line endings are LF in the repository AND in every working tree, on every platform.
#
# This is not a style preference.  `etc/settings` is an Isabelle component settings file,
# which bash SOURCES.  When bash sources a CRLF file, the trailing carriage return becomes
# part of the last token on the line, so
#
#     ISABELLE_SEMANTIC_EMBEDDING_HOME="$COMPONENT"
#
# assigns the component path plus a CR.  The next line appends "/lib/semantic_embedding.jar"
# to it, putting the CR in the MIDDLE of a path, and Isabelle rejects the classpath with
#
#     *** Illegal char <\r> at index 100: ...isabelle-semantic-embedding<CR>\lib\...jar
#
# after which EVERY Scala-backed entry point fails -- `isabelle build` could not build any
# session at all, not even HOL.
#
# How it happened: the win-64 conda leg runs on windows-latest, where git's core.autocrlf
# defaults to true, so actions/checkout rewrote this LF file to CRLF; the recipe then
# copied those bytes into the package verbatim.  The linux and macOS legs were unaffected,
# which is why the same source produced one broken artifact out of five.  Shipped as
# isabelle-semantic-embedding 0.1.1 and found only when isabelle-minilang's Windows smoke
# could not register its own component.
#
# `text=auto eol=lf` covers the whole tree rather than just etc/settings, because the same
# hazard applies to anything else a shell or Isabelle reads, and because the file that
# bites you is the one nobody thought to list.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Genuinely binary: never touch these.
*.jar    binary
*.so     binary
*.dylib  binary
*.dll    binary
*.zst    binary
*.png    binary
*.pdf    binary
